reviews.review_text:
Patcher This recording apparently comes from the same line that I recorded back in 84. The mixer used was a Yamaha and it was recorded from the 10th row just off the isle on the right. 

The system was a combination of two tapers from that I recorded with for SPAC in 1983 and when I met up with them here we used their system and my seats. I had FOB for all three nights, ranging from 10 to 14th row center. I really glad that another copy of this has surfaced since my second set was recorded on a Memorex metal tape, which developed drop outs over the years. It is nice to get a clean copy!!!!!!!!!

All 3 nights were very, very good!
